 <purpose>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the definition of basic topological constructs with associated geometry. 
 Geometric curves are, as originally defined, unbounded and are bounded by vertices to form edge curves. In a similar way unbounded surfaces are bounded by loops of edges to form faces.
 </purpose>

